<br>
If you don't know the person then your risking not getting your item back.  Hate to say it but we have all seen that there are a few less then honest folks out there.<br>
<br>
Had someone loot a no drop item also.  Now if it is their first time in a dungeon this can be understandable.  I started to loot on my first dungeon adventure and the no drop window came up, thank goodness.  <br>
But when the one who does it has already told the group that they have been on several adventures, then I would say that person is simple taking the loot and using the excuse that their no drop window was turned off.<br>
